sense single-stranded RNA","Negative sense single-stranded RNA","Double-stranded DNA","Double-stranded RNA","Single-stranded DNA"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ERetroviruses contain \u003Cstrong\u003Epositive sense single-stranded RNA\u003C/strong\u003E as their genetic material. This RNA genome must be converted to DNA by the viral enzyme reverse transcriptase before viral replication can proceed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENegative sense single-stranded RNA\u003C/strong\u003E - While some viruses use this format, retroviruses use positive sense RNA\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDouble-stranded DNA\u003C/strong\u003E - DNA is produced during replication but is not the initial genetic material\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDouble-stranded RNA\u003C/strong\u003E - This is found in reoviruses but not retroviruses\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESingle-stranded DNA\u003C/strong\u003E - This is found in parvoviruses but not retroviruses\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter entering the cell, the RNA genome is reverse transcribed into DNA, which then integrates into the host genome using viral integrase. Only after integration can viral proteins be synthesised using host cell machinery.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Retroviruses contain positive sense single-stranded RNA as their genetic material","Retroviruses must convert their RNA genome to DNA using reverse transcriptase before protein synthesis can occur","Integration into the host genome by integrase is required before viral proteins can be produced"],"references":["Chameettachal A, Mustafa F, Rizvi TA. Understanding Retroviral Life Cycle and its Genomic RNA Packaging. J Mol Biol. 2023 Feb 1;435(3):167924. doi: 10.1016/j.jmb.2022.167924. Epub 2022 Dec 16. PMID: 36535429.","Sastry, A. S., \u0026 Bhat, S. (2018). Essentials of medical microbiology. JP Medical Ltd","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51908"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14967"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51908"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T09:51:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-30T09:52:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7655"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66457"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4936","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4936"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f","name":"Immune System","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"cre